com.opengamma.strata.product

Class SecurityLink<P extends Product>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.product.SecurityLink<P>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of the product
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Link<Security<P>>, Resolvable<SecurityLink<P>>, StandardIdentifiable, Serializable, Bean, ImmutableBean

    public final class SecurityLink<P extends Product>
extends Object
implements Link<Security<P>>, Resolvable<SecurityLink<P>>, ImmutableBean, Serializable
    A link to a security.

    A security link provides loose coupling between different parts of the object model. For example, an equity trade can hold a link to the underlying equity. The two objects can be updated independently of each other. If the link resolver supports historic versions, then the correct version of the target will be returned when resolved.

    A link can be in one of two states, resolvable and resolved. In the resolvable state, the link contains the identifier and product type of the security. In the resolved state, the link directly embeds the security.

    To obtain the target of the link, the resolve(LinkResolver) method must be used. When the link is in the resolved state, the resolver is not used. When the link is in the resolvable state, the resolver is invoked.

    The LinkResolver is a simple interface that is implemented to find the security by identifier. It can be implemented in many ways, including an in-memory map, a database or a call to another service. The resolver throws a LinkResolutionException if the security cannot be found.

    See Also:
    StandardLink, Serialized Form

        public static <R extends Product> SecurityLink<R> resolvable(StandardId identifier,
                                                             Class<R> productType)
        Create a resolvable link for the specified identifier and product type.

        The returned link will be in the resolvable state, containing the identifier and product type. When the resolve(LinkResolver) method is called, the resolver will be used to find the security, for example from a database.

        Parameters:
        identifier - the primary identifier of the security
        productType - the type of the product
        Returns:
        a new resolvable link

      • resolved

        public static <R extends Product> SecurityLink<R> resolved(Security<R> target)
        Create a link with the security embedded directly.

        The returned link will be in the resolved state, directly embedding the security. When the resolve(LinkResolver) method is called, the embedded target will be returned without needing to use the resolver.

        Parameters:
        target - the target security
        Returns:
        a new resolved link

      • resolve

        public Security<P> resolve(LinkResolver resolver)
        Resolves this link using the specified resolver.

        The resolver is used to find the linked security. In the resolvable state, the resolver is used to find the security, throwing an exception if the security cannot be found. In the resolved state, the directly embedded security is returned without using the resolver.

        The returned target may contain other unresolved links. Use resolveLinks(LinkResolver) to fully resolve the object graph.

        Specified by:
        resolve in interface Link<Security<P extends Product>>
        Parameters:
        resolver - the resolver to use for the resolution
        Returns:
        the security
        Throws:
        LinkResolutionException - if the security cannot be resolved

      • resolveLinks

        public SecurityLink<P> resolveLinks(LinkResolver resolver)
        Resolves this link, and any links that the security contains, using the specified resolver.

        First, the security is resolved using resolve(LinkResolver). Second, if the security implements Resolvable, it is resolved as well. The returned security should not contain any unresolved links.

        An exception is thrown if a link cannot be resolved.

        Specified by:
        resolveLinks in interface Resolvable<SecurityLink<P extends Product>>
        Parameters:
        resolver - the resolver to use for the resolution
        Returns:
        the fully resolved link
        Throws:
        LinkResolutionException - if a link cannot be resolved
